The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Guj Ambuja net soars to Rs 298 cr

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, April 17: Gujarat Ambuja Cements has posted a 109 per cent jump in net profit to Rs 298.59 crore for the third quarter ended March 31 from Rs 143.11 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

 The total turnover of the company increased by 39 per cent to Rs 924.29 crore from Rs 667.24 crore in the year-ago period.

 Total income (net of excise) increased from Rs 675 crore to Rs 978.13 crore, a growth of 45 per cent.

 The company sold 3.65 million tonnes of cement against 3.19 million tonnes in the same period last fiscal, a growth of 14 per cent.

 On a consolidated basis, the group has posted a net profit of Rs 315 crore for the quarter against Rs 155.60 crore in the year-ago period, a growth of 102 per cent. Total income rose to Rs 989.65 crore from Rs 910.32 crore. 

 The board has declared an interim dividend of 50 per cent or Re 1 per share. 

 The companys stock spurted 8.28 per cent today on the Bombay Stock Exchange to close at Rs 117.75 against the previous close of Rs 108.75 as 52,17,329 shares changed hands.

 Swiss cement major, Holcim, which had acquired a 14.8 per cent stake in the company for Rs 105 per share from its promoters, is making an open offer to the public to acquire up to 27.43 crore shares with a face value of Rs 2 each. This represents an aggregate of 20.28 per cent of the fully paid-up equity capital of the company. The offer begins on April 19 and closes on April 24. The open offer price was set at around Rs 90 per share.

 According to the company, 2005-06 has been a good year for the economy with a likely growth of around 8 per cent. The cement demand across the country is strong with most parts of the country witnessing a double-digit growth resulting in cement despatch growth of over 11 per cent for the year.

 The company has given a strong future outlook and expects the growth to continue in the wake of robust construction and infrastructure development in the country.

 Indo Rama profit jumps

 Indo Rama Textiles Ltd has reported a 63.50 per cent increase in net profit year-on-year at Rs 11.38 crore during the fourth quarter of this fiscal ended March 31 on net sales revenue of Rs 95.64 crore, which is down by 5.30 per cent.

 The textile companys operating profit rose by 29.7 per cent at Rs 21.09 crore during this quarter.

 In 2005-06, Indo Rama Textiles has registered a 70.19 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 20.90 crore against Rs 12.28 crore during the previous fiscal. Its net sales revenue, however, declined by 4.84 per cent at Rs 372.98 crore during the period. 




